---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Narrows — About"
  description="The Narrows is a trade risk intelligence resource. The due diligence step before a deal closes, a policy locks in, or a facility is underwritten."
>

<style>
.about-hero {
  background: var(--navy);
  padding: 128px var(--s4) var(--s6);
  border-bottom: 3px solid var(--gold);
}
.about-hero-inner {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
}
.about-hero-title {
  font-size: clamp(32px, 4vw, 50px);
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--white);
  line-height: 1.1;
  letter-spacing: -0.025em;
  margin-bottom: var(--s4);
}
.about-hero-title em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--gold); }
.about-hero-body {
  font-size: 17px;
  color: rgba(255,255,255,0.55);
  line-height: 1.8;
  font-weight: 300;
  max-width: 620px;
}
.about-hero-body strong { color: rgba(255,255,255,0.85); font-weight: 500; }

.about-wrap {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: var(--s6) var(--s4);
}
.about-section {
  padding-bottom: var(--s5);
  margin-bottom: var(--s5);
  border-bottom: var(--rule-light);
}
.about-section:last-of-type { border-bottom: none; }

.about-eyebrow {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  font-size: 10px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--blue);
  margin-bottom: var(--s2);
}
.about-eyebrow::before {
  content: '';
  width: 16px;
  height: 2px;
  background: var(--gold);
  display: inline-block;
}
.about-section-title {
  font-size: clamp(20px, 2.5vw, 28px);
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--navy);
  line-height: 1.2;
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
  margin-bottom: var(--s3);
}
.about-body {
  font-size: 16px;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.85;
  font-weight: 300;
}
.about-body p { margin-bottom: var(--s3); }
.about-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }
.about-body strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 500; }

/* Principle list */
.principle-list {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  margin-top: var(--s3);
}
.principle-item {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 24px 1fr;
  gap: var(--s2);
  padding: var(--s2) 0;
  border-bottom: var(--rule-light);
}
.principle-item:first-child { border-top: var(--rule-light); }
.principle-mark {
  width: 6px;
  height: 6px;
  background: var(--gold);
  border-radius: 1px;
  margin-top: 9px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}
.principle-text {
  font-size: 15px;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.75;
  font-weight: 300;
}
.principle-text strong { color: var(--text-primary); font-weight: 600; }

/* Contact */
.contact-block {
  background: var(--surface);
  border: var(--rule-light);
  border-left: 3px solid var(--gold);
  border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
  padding: var(--s3) var(--s4);
  margin-top: var(--s4);
}
.contact-label {
  font-size: 9px;
  font-weight: 700;
  letter-spacing: 0.14em;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  color: var(--blue);
  margin-bottom: 8px;
}
.contact-email {
  font-size: 22px;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--navy);
  text-decoration: none;
  display: block;
  margin-bottom: 4px;
  transition: color 0.15s;
}
.contact-email:hover { color: var(--blue); }
.contact-sub {
  font-size: 13px;
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-weight: 300;
}

/* CTA */
.about-cta {
  background: var(--navy);
  border-top: 3px solid var(--gold);
  padding: var(--s5) var(--s4);
}
.about-cta-inner {
  max-width: 800px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: space-between;
  gap: var(--s4);
  flex-wrap: wrap;
}
.about-cta-text {
  font-size: clamp(18px, 2.5vw, 26px);
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--white);
  line-height: 1.25;
  letter-spacing: -0.01em;
}
.about-cta-text em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--gold); }

@media (max-width: 700px) {
  .about-cta-inner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; }
}
</style>

<!-- HERO -->
<div class="about-hero">
  <div class="about-hero-inner">
    <div class="eyebrow" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.35);">
      <span style="background:var(--gold);width:16px;height:2px;display:inline-block;margin-right:8px;vertical-align:middle;flex-shrink:0;"></span>
      About The Narrows
    </div>
    <h1 class="about-hero-title">
      The due diligence step<br>
      that most risk models<br>
      <em>do not include.</em>
    </h1>
    <p class="about-hero-body">
      The Narrows is a trade risk intelligence resource. <strong>It exists to be run before a deal closes, a policy locks in, or a facility is underwritten.</strong> Not as a monitoring tool. Not as a dashboard. As the step that answers the structural question behind the transaction.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- BODY -->
<div class="about-wrap">

  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-eyebrow">The premise</div>
    <h2 class="about-section-title">Most risk pricing does not reflect the underlying structure of supply chain constraints.</h2>
    <div class="about-body">
      <p>AIS tracks vessels. PortWatch tracks throughput. Index providers track freight rates. These are monitoring tools. They tell you what is happening to traffic. They do not tell you which bilateral supply chains depend on which corridors, at what percentage of total supply, or what a credible alternative looks like and what it costs.</p>
      <p>The Narrows operates at a different layer. It models the structural exposure of importing countries to specific trade corridors, denominated in dollars, at the (importer, corridor, commodity) level. The output is not a signal. It is a number that belongs in a risk model, a credit facility, or an underwriting decision.</p>
      <p>The world is generating new constraint points. Chokepoints, ports, borders, shipping lanes that once functioned as frictionless infrastructure are becoming risk variables. As the globalised order fragments and national interests assert themselves, the geography of trade is becoming a risk factor in ways that most models have not yet priced. <strong>The Narrows is built to measure that.</strong></p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-eyebrow">The name</div>
    <h2 class="about-section-title">The points where the world narrows.</h2>
    <div class="about-body">
      <p>The name refers to the points where constraints are hard, data has meaning, and decisions cannot be deferred. A strait through which 30% of global seaborne trade passes is a narrow. A port that handles the majority of a country's grain imports is a narrow. A corridor that has no viable alternative is a narrow.</p>
      <p>At these points, the structure of the world becomes legible. The dependencies are real. The exposure is quantifiable. The decisions that flow from understanding them are consequential. That is where The Narrows works.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-eyebrow">What The Narrows is building</div>
    <h2 class="about-section-title">The Chokepoint Dependency Model is the first tool in a broader suite.</h2>
    <div class="about-body">
      <p>The current model covers 22 maritime risk corridors, $1.8 trillion in matched trade value, 85 importing countries, and 7 commodity classes. It produces three outputs: value at risk, rerouting penalty, and fleet at risk. Every assumption is substitutable.</p>
      <p>The practice is building toward a broader suite of tools covering port risk, event monitoring, and exposure analysis across trade corridors and supply chain infrastructure. The analytical framework is not limited to maritime trade. The same approach applies wherever hard constraints concentrate risk and data has real-world implications.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-eyebrow">How it works</div>
    <h2 class="about-section-title">Every demo is a live session. Every assumption is yours to change.</h2>
    <div class="about-body">
      <p>The Narrows is not a self-serve product. Access is through a demo session in which the model is run against the specific counterparties, corridors, and commodities relevant to the decision at hand. Every parameter the model uses can be replaced with the client's own assumptions.</p>
      <p>Full model documentation, including corridor definitions, the complete dependency matrix, and the simulation architecture, is available under NDA for qualified counterparties.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="principle-list">
      <div class="principle-item">
        <div class="principle-mark"></div>
        <div class="principle-text"><strong>Assumptions are stated, not buried.</strong> Every output identifies the parameters behind it. If the defaults differ from the client's view, that is a one-parameter change in the session.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-item">
        <div class="principle-mark"></div>
        <div class="principle-text"><strong>Limitations are documented.</strong> The methodology page states clearly what the model does and does not do. A professional who understands the limits is better placed to use the outputs.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-item">
        <div class="principle-mark"></div>
        <div class="principle-text"><strong>The analysis precedes the conversation.</strong> The papers published on this site are not marketing materials. They are model outputs applied to live events, with every assumption stated. They exist so that a prospective client can evaluate the work before requesting access.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="principle-item">
        <div class="principle-mark"></div>
        <div class="principle-text"><strong>No sales funnel.</strong> A person responds to every enquiry. There is no CRM sequence, no free trial tier, and no self-serve onboarding. Access is a conversation.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="about-section">
    <div class="about-eyebrow">Contact</div>
    <h2 class="about-section-title">One address. A person replies.</h2>
    <div class="about-body">
      <p>All enquiries — demo requests, press, research collaboration, methodology questions — go to the same address. Response time is typically within one business day.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="contact-block">
      <div class="contact-label">Direct contact</div>
      <a href="mailto:fysh@narrows.io" class="contact-email">fysh@narrows.io</a>
      <div class="contact-sub">The Narrows · Trade Risk Intelligence · narrows.io</div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>

<!-- CTA -->
<div class="about-cta">
  <div class="about-cta-inner">
    <div class="about-cta-text">
      The news tells you what happened.<br>
      <em>The Narrows tells you what it costs.</em>
    </div>
    <a href="mailto:fysh@narrows.io?subject=Demo request — The Narrows&body=Organisation:%0ARole:%0APrimary corridor of interest:%0A%0AContext (optional):" class="btn btn-gold">Request a demo</a>
  </div>
</div>

</BaseLayout>
